{
  "specVersion": "0.1",
  "domain": {
    "name": "dynamic_workflow_engine",
    "description": "A data-driven workflow engine (Pega/Appian-class): an intake questionnaire resolves to a Scenario from a library; a generic orchestrator instantiates it and decomposes it into tasks routed to users. N-invariant \u2014 the engine loads ONE scenario per instance; the library is data. NO native ODC BPT (can't define processes at runtime); the process is a state machine in data + engine service actions. The engine/UI/loader are FIXED code; scenarios are rows. See ARCHITECTURE.md.",
    "entities": [
      {
        "name": "TaskTemplate",
        "context": "workflow",
        "naturalKey": "Code",
        "attributes": [
          {
            "name": "Code",
            "dataType": "Text",
            "mandatory": true
          },
          {
            "name": "Name",
            "dataType": "Text",
            "mandatory": true
          },
          {
            "name": "Type",
            "dataType": "Text"
          },
          {
            "name": "FieldDefinition",
            "dataType": "Text",
            "length": 2000
          },
          {
            "name": "DefaultRole",
            "dataType": "Text"
          },
          {
            "name": "SlaHours",
            "dataType": "Integer"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "Scenario",
        "context": "workflow",
        "naturalKey": "Code",
        "attributes": [
          {
            "name": "Code",
            "dataType": "Text",
            "mandatory": true
          },
          {
            "name": "Name",
            "dataType": "Text",
            "mandatory": true
          },
          {
            "name": "EntryCriteria",
            "dataType": "Text"
          },
          {
            "name": "Status",
            "dataType": "Text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "ScenarioStep",
        "context": "workflow",
        "references": [
          "Scenario",
          "TaskTemplate"
        ],
        "attributes": [
          {
            "name": "Sequence",
            "dataType": "Integer",
            "mandatory": true
          },
          {
            "name": "ParallelGroup",
            "dataType": "Text"
          },
          {
            "name": "DependsOnStep",
            "dataType": "Text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "TransitionRule",
        "context": "workflow",
        "references": [
          "Scenario"
        ],
        "attributes": [
          {
            "name": "FromStep",
            "dataType": "Text",
            "mandatory": true
          },
          {
            "name": "ToStep",
            "dataType": "Text",
            "mandatory": true
          },
          {
            "name": "Condition",
            "dataType": "Text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "DecisionRow",
        "context": "workflow",
        "references": [
          "Scenario"
        ],
        "attributes": [
          {
            "name": "MatchExpression",
            "dataType": "Text",
            "mandatory": true
          },
          {
            "name": "Priority",
            "dataType": "Integer"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "WorkflowInstance",
        "context": "workflow",
        "references": [
          "Scenario"
        ],
        "naturalKey": "InstanceNo",
        "attributes": [
          {
            "name": "InstanceNo",
            "dataType": "Text",
            "mandatory": true
          },
          {
            "name": "State",
            "dataType": "Text"
          },
          {
            "name": "Context",
            "dataType": "Text",
            "length": 2000
          },
          {
            "name": "StartedBy",
            "dataType": "Text"
          },
          {
            "name": "StartedAt",
            "dataType": "Text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "TaskInstance",
        "context": "workflow",
        "references": [
          "WorkflowInstance",
          "TaskTemplate"
        ],
        "attributes": [
          {
            "name": "Assignee",
            "dataType": "Text"
          },
          {
            "name": "Status",
            "dataType": "Text"
          },
          {
            "name": "InputData",
            "dataType": "Text",
            "length": 2000
          },
          {
            "name": "OutputData",
            "dataType": "Text",
            "length": 2000
          },
          {
            "name": "DueAt",
            "dataType": "Text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "AuditEvent",
        "context": "workflow",
        "references": [
          "WorkflowInstance"
        ],
        "attributes": [
          {
            "name": "Description",
            "dataType": "Text",
            "mandatory": true
          },
          {
            "name": "Actor",
            "dataType": "Text"
          },
          {
            "name": "At",
            "dataType": "Text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "actors": [
      "requester",
      "worker",
      "admin"
    ],
    "capabilities": [
      {
        "name": "SubmitIntake",
        "actor": "requester",
        "reads": [
          "DecisionRow",
          "Scenario"
        ],
        "writes": [
          "WorkflowInstance",
          "TaskInstance",
          "AuditEvent"
        ],
        "service": "SubmitIntake",
        "raisesEvent": "InstanceStarted",
        "engine": true,
        "note": "questionnaire answers -> ResolveScenario (DecisionRow match) -> InstantiateWorkflow (spawn first TaskInstance(s))"
      },
      {
        "name": "ResolveScenario",
        "actor": "requester",
        "reads": [
          "DecisionRow",
          "Scenario"
        ],
        "service": "ResolveScenario",
        "engine": true,
        "note": "FIXED: indexed decision-table match of intake answers -> Scenario. N-invariant (lookup, not scan)."
      },
      {
        "name": "AdvanceInstance",
        "reads": [
          "WorkflowInstance",
          "Scenario",
          "ScenarioStep",
          "TransitionRule",
          "TaskInstance"
        ],
        "writes": [
          "TaskInstance",
          "WorkflowInstance",
          "AuditEvent"
        ],
        "service": "AdvanceInstance",
        "engine": true,
        "note": "FIXED ENGINE (G1): on task completion, traverse THIS instance's ScenarioSteps + eval TransitionRules -> spawn next TaskInstance(s) (parallel groups), update State, write audit. Loads one scenario; N-invariant."
      },
      {
        "name": "CompleteTask",
        "actor": "worker",
        "reads": [
          "TaskInstance"
        ],
        "writes": [
          "TaskInstance",
          "AuditEvent"
        ],
        "service": "CompleteTask",
        "callsService": "AdvanceInstance",
        "engine": true,
        "note": "worker submits a task's OutputData -> CompleteTask -> AdvanceInstance."
      },
      {
        "name": "ClaimTask",
        "actor": "worker",
        "reads": [
          "TaskInstance"
        ],
        "writes": [
          "TaskInstance"
        ],
        "service": "ClaimTask"
      },
      {
        "name": "MyWork",
        "actor": "worker",
        "reads": [
          "TaskInstance",
          "WorkflowInstance",
          "TaskTemplate"
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "TrackInstance",
        "actor": "requester",
        "reads": [
          "WorkflowInstance",
          "TaskInstance",
          "AuditEvent"
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "AuthorLibrary",
        "actor": "admin",
        "reads": [
          "TaskTemplate",
          "Scenario",
          "ScenarioStep",
          "TransitionRule",
          "DecisionRow"
        ],
        "writes": [
          "TaskTemplate",
          "Scenario",
          "ScenarioStep",
          "TransitionRule",
          "DecisionRow"
        ],
        "service": "SaveLibraryElement",
        "note": "the client maintains the scenario library (any N) without code."
      },
      {
        "name": "ComposeInstance",
        "reads": [
          "TaskTemplate",
          "WorkflowInstance"
        ],
        "writes": [
          "WorkflowInstance",
          "ScenarioStep",
          "AuditEvent"
        ],
        "service": "ComposeInstance",
        "engine": true,
        "note": "FIXED (G5): assemble an instance-specific ScenarioStep graph from GOVERNED TaskTemplates (select/order/route). Called by the IntakeAgent. Composition only \u2014 never invents a task."
      },
      {
        "name": "ValidateComposition",
        "reads": [
          "ScenarioStep",
          "TaskTemplate",
          "WorkflowInstance"
        ],
        "writes": [
          "AuditEvent"
        ],
        "service": "ValidateComposition",
        "engine": true,
        "note": "FIXED (G5): deterministic gate BEFORE an instance runs \u2014 every step resolves to a real TaskTemplate, routing roles exist, required controls present, no orphan/cycle, SLAs sane. Invalid -> reject for agent revision. Nothing runs unvalidated."
      },
      {
        "name": "AgenticIntake",
        "orchestrates": true,
        "triggerEvent": "IntakeStarted",
        "steps": [
          {
            "name": "Compose",
            "ai": "IntakeComposer",
            "reads": [
              "TaskTemplate"
            ],
            "writes": [
              "ScenarioStep"
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "Validate",
            "callsService": "ValidateComposition"
          },
          {
            "name": "Instantiate",
            "callsService": "InstantiateWorkflow"
          }
        ],
        "note": "G4: the agentic intake as a short compose->validate->instantiate orchestration. The Compose step is an AIAgent (IntakeComposer) that assembles the workflow from GOVERNED TaskTemplates; Validate is the deterministic gate; Instantiate spawns the first tasks. Replaces the static ResolveScenario for emergent (N->0 pre-authored) scenarios; the fixed engine + dynamic UI are unchanged. The orchestration SHELL is static (one process); the DYNAMISM is the agent's composed output. Risk-tiered approval sits between Validate and Instantiate; fully audited + reproducible."
      },
      {
        "name": "EscalateOverdue",
        "orchestrates": true,
        "triggerEvent": "SlaSweep",
        "steps": [
          {
            "name": "FindOverdue",
            "reads": [
              "TaskInstance"
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "Escalate",
            "callsService": "AdvanceInstance"
          }
        ],
        "note": "Timer-driven SLA/escalation sweep (the ONLY timer; not per-instance flow)."
      }
    ],
    "integrations": [
      {
        "name": "IdP",
        "kind": "identity",
        "purpose": "SSO/roles",
        "stub": true
      },
      {
        "name": "LibrarySource",
        "kind": "consume",
        "purpose": "bulk-load the scenario library (ETL from Appian/Pega/sheets) \u2014 G3",
        "stub": true
      },
      {
        "name": "Notify",
        "kind": "consume",
        "purpose": "task assignment / SLA notifications",
        "stub": true
      }
    ],
    "libraries": [
      "WorkflowDesignSystem"
    ],
    "_harness_gaps": {
      "note": "The capabilities flagged engine:true map to a NEW canonical `workflow-engine` recipe (G1) \u2014 one fixed implementation parameterized by entity names, NOT per-scenario. The WorkspacePortal's task screen needs a NEW `dynamic-form` recipe (G2) that renders TaskTemplate.FieldDefinition at runtime via a fixed field-type set. The library rows load via a bulk importer (G3, generalize the deterministic-SQL/REST seed). Everything else uses existing recipes. SPIKE the dynamic form UX first."
    }
  }
}
